layerGroup.name: backscatter_comp
layerGroup.title: Multi-resolution acoustic reflectance of the Australian margin (CSIRO/NESP)
layerGroup.abstractTxt:
A collation of seabed backscatter data from multibeam bathymetry surveys of the Australian margin held by CSIRO in or around 2010. The layer group includes data gridded at both low (~300m) and high (~30m) resolutions, with higher-resolution data prioritised where overlaps occur.
The acoustic reflectance intensity has been harmonised across surveys to provide a continuous representation of seabed hardness, with darker areas indicating likely reef (acoustically "harder") and paler areas representing likely sediments (acoustically "softer").
